---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import Math from '../components/Math.astro'
import { sourceFile } from '../data/site'
---

<BaseLayout title="Foundations">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Foundations</p>

      <h1>Conformal structures, densities, and formal ambient calculus.</h1>

      <p>
        The foundational layer provides the abstract objects used by later
        GJMS, Fefferman–Graham, and Poincaré–Einstein developments.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="site-shell grid-2">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Conformal Structure</h3>

        <p>
          A conformal structure records a positive ray of compatible metrics
          over each point. A chosen scale selects one representative.
        </p>

        <Math display tex="\mathcal G \to M" />

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Conformal/Basic.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open Basic.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Conformal Densities</h3>

        <p>
          Densities are represented both through scale-dependent descriptions
          and equivariant functions on the metric bundle.
        </p>

        <Math display tex="F(\delta_r u)=\chi(r)F(u)" />

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Conformal/Density.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open Density.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Ambient Bundle</h3>

        <p>
          The formal ambient carrier extends the metric bundle by the normal
          coordinate <Math tex="\rho" />.
        </p>

        <Math display tex="\widetilde{\mathcal G}=\mathcal G\times\mathbb R_\rho" />

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/Ambientbasic.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open Ambientbasic.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Formal Ambient Calculus</h3>

        <p>
          The formal calculus stores the defining function <Math tex="Q" />,
          the dilation field <Math tex="X" />, and Laplacian identities as
          explicit algebraic laws.
        </p>

        <Math display tex="XQ=2Q" />

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/Ambientoperator.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open Ambientoperator.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section border-top">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <div class="note">
        This layer intentionally separates abstract interfaces and certified
        algebraic identities from a future full tensor-calculus realization.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>